e guanylation) lack direct experimental validation in abiotic contexts.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [ \"rxn_010\", \"rxn_011\" ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Flag these as hypothetical/unvalidated steps and seek supporting (if indirect) literature\",\n        \"Add notes on plausibility gaps based on prebiotic chemistry hurdles\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P6\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_009\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_013\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_012\": 0.9\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.9,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.8,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.8,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.6,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.8,\n      \"feedback\": \"Direct UV-driven synthesis of guanidine and urea is well-supported. However, this does not close the loop to arginine explicitly, merely provides lateral chemical supply. The route plays an important role in network robustness but does not by itself deliver the target.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Explicitly link guanidine formation into subsequent pathways, if possible\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P7\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_002\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.8,\n        \"rxn_005\": 0.88\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.87,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.85,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.89,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.8,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.87,\n      \"feedback\": \"A good redundant path feeding in at the \u03b2-aminopropionitrile/ornithine hub. Chemically sound, each step exists in the literature, and network connections are robust.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Indicate where mineral catalysis (e.g., pyrite, montmorillonite) could support transformations\"\n      ]\n    },\n   